<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="8" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[192,1440,611,668]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,324,611,635]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Remarks.</emphasis>
This is the most distinctive species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Crotch" authorityYear="1873" box="[805,1008,611,635]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Cephaloscymnus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[805,1008,611,635]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Cephaloscymnus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of green tinted elytra and wide, yellow, lateral pronotal margin. Male genitalia are also unique within the genus.
</paragraph>
